The paper deals with the problem of predicting the existence and number of salient objects in an image using holistic cues, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for this task also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for annotation, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the applications of the proposed model in salient object detection and image retrieval suggest a connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
